quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  12,7,In Yusuf and his brothers there are Signs for every one of those who wants to ask
  12,8,"When they declared, ´Why! Yusuf and his brother are dearer to our father than we are although we constitute a powerful group. Our father is clearly making a mistake"
  12,9,Kill Yusuf or expel him to some land so that your father will look to you alone and then you can be people who do right.´
  12,10,"One of them said, ´Do not take Yusuf´s life but throw him to the bottom of the well, so that some travellers may discover him, if this is something that you have to do.´"
  12,11,"They said, ´Our father! What is wrong with you that you refuse to trust us with Yusuf when in truth we only wish him well"
  12,12,Why don´t you send him out with us tomorrow so he can enjoy himself and play about? All of us will make sure that he is safe.´
  12,13,"He said, ´It grieves me to let him go with you I fear a wolf might come and eat him up while you are heedless, not attending him.´"
  12,14,"They said, ´If a wolf does come and eat him up when together we make up a powerful group in that case we would truly be in loss!´"
  12,15,"But when, in fact, they did go out with him and gathered all together and agreed to put him at the bottom of the well, We then revealed to him that: ´You will inform them of this deed they perpetrate at a time when they are totally unaware.´"
  12,16,That night they came back to their father in tears
  12,17,"saying, ´Father, we went out to run a race and left Yusuf together with our things and then a wolf appeared and ate him up but you are never going to believe us now, not even though we really tell the truth.´"
  12,18,"They then produced his shirt with false blood on it. He said, ´It is merely that your lower selves have suggested something to you which you did; but beauty lies in showing steadfastness. It is Allah alone who is my Help in face of the event that you describe.´"
  12,19,"Some travellers came that way and then dispatched their water-drawer who let his bucket down. He said, ´Good news for me, I´ve found a boy!´ They then hid him away among their goods. Allah knew very well what they were doing"
  12,20,"They sold him for a pittance, a few small coins, considering him to be of little worth"